text: thanks!!!! alot i did it obviously with your help, i was trying to build an tkinter GUI with a face recognition algoritm dlib, i had alot of errors, but now i did it, the last thing to solve was an error with tkinter i dont know why but in the lib folder (executable) the library tkinter was named "Tkinter" i just change to "tkinter" and run again and it works, i let my setup.py version. cheers from Colombia!! """ Created on Mon May 18 15:03:55 2020  @author: scart """  from cx_Freeze import setup, Executable import sys import tkinter import cv2 import numpy as np import PIL.Image, PIL.ImageTk import dlib  base=None if sys.platform == 'win32':     base="Win32GUI"  setup(name = 'GUI',       version = '1.0',       description = 'Detector de pupila',       options = {"build_exe":{"packages":{"tkinter","cv2","dlib","numpy","PIL.Image","PIL.ImageTk"},"include_files":["shape_predictor_68_face_landmarks.dat","GPS_logo100x100.jpg","somos_udi_logo400x400.jpg"]}},       executables = [Executable("GUI_Seguidor_pupila1.py",base=base)])

text: There will be an import statement for sure. Whole data fetch process in the app is based on sql queries and presenting obtained data via label lists and graphs. It's somewhat prototype for later server-based one.  Initially, I wanted to create .db beforehand and attach it to compiled via cx_freeze program.
